      <h3>Key Features</h3>

      <h4>Multi-Channel Deployment</h4>
      <p>A single trained chatbot can simultaneously serve a website widget, WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, Instagram DMs, Telegram, Slack, and email. The vendor states there are no per-channel fees — one subscription covers all channels. This is one of the platform's clearer differentiators compared to chatbot builders that charge per channel or per platform.</p>

      <h4>Knowledge Source Controls</h4>
      <p>Users can choose between three knowledge modes: restrict the chatbot to trained content only, allow it to supplement with ChatGPT's general knowledge, or enable live internet search. This gives granular control over whether the chatbot stays strictly within documented material or can draw on broader information.</p>

      <h4>Human Handoff &amp; Live Chat</h4>
      <p>On the Business plan ($89/month) and above, the chatbot can offer to transfer a conversation to a human agent when it cannot find an answer. The agent receives the full conversation transcript and can continue from where the AI left off. Availability hours can be configured so handoff only happens during staffed periods.</p>

      <h4>Automated Retraining</h4>
      <p>Available on Business plan and above. The system revisits selected website sources on a daily, weekly, or monthly schedule and updates the chatbot's knowledge when content changes. Manual retraining is available on all plans. The extent to which this correctly identifies and applies content changes without introducing errors would require hands-on testing to evaluate.</p>

      <h4>Lead Capture &amp; CRM Integration</h4>
      <p>Built-in lead forms collect contact details during conversations. Leads are stored in the dashboard and can be emailed to team members. However, syncing leads to a CRM requires setting up Zapier or Make workflows — there is no native one-click CRM connector (except for Shopify, which has deeper native integration).</p>

      <h4>Zapier MCP AI Actions</h4>
      <p>Through the Zapier integration (via MCP), the chatbot can perform real-world actions during conversations: submitting forms, booking appointments, sending emails and SMS messages, and checking order status. This extends the platform beyond passive Q&amp;A into basic agentic functionality.</p>

      <h3>Areas Requiring Hands-On Validation</h3>
      <p>Several important performance characteristics cannot be assessed from documentation alone. These include: response quality and accuracy across different LLMs on the same training data, hallucination resistance when restricted to trained content only, the effectiveness of the auto retraining feature when content changes, multilingual accuracy (the platform claims 95 languages), and performance under concurrent conversations. These are noted as open questions from the research and would benefit from real product testing.</p>
