      <h2>User Experience</h2>
      <h3>Setup Process</h3>
      <p>The vendor claims setup in "under 5 minutes." The process involves creating a free account, entering a website URL or uploading documents, customising the chatbot's appearance and prompt, and pasting a JavaScript snippet onto the target website. A free install service is available for users who need assistance. Setup is designed for non-technical users with no coding required.</p>

      <h3>Daily Usage</h3>
      <p>Ongoing activity centers on monitoring chat conversations through the dashboard's History panel, reviewing lead capture data, and refining the chatbot's prompt and knowledge sources based on real interactions. The Knowledge Assistant (Business+ plan) flags unanswered questions, suggesting content gaps to address.</p>

      <h3>Learning Curve</h3>
      <p>The platform is marketed primarily to non-technical business owners. Configuration is prompt-based and settings-driven — there is no visual conversation flow builder. Users who are comfortable writing instructions in plain English should find the interface approachable. Users accustomed to drag-and-drop flow builders (such as those found in Botpress or Voiceflow) may find the configuration model less familiar.</p>

      <h3>Interface &amp; Usability</h3>
      <p>We did not get hands-on access to the dashboard, so interface usability is assessed from available documentation. The feature descriptions suggest a control panel organised by chatbot, with tabs for training sources, prompt configuration, chat history, lead capture settings, and integration connections. The pricing comparison table on the public site is clear and well-structured, suggesting attention to information design that likely carries into the product interface.</p>
